      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must replicate COU geometry, fluid, and operating envelope; any geometric or physiological differences must be quantified and their impact on hemolysis prediction assessed.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry, which is representative but not identical to the specific VAD device. Fluid was bovine blood rather than human blood; hematocrit matched. No sensitivity analysis quantifies the impact of species-specific blood rheology on NIH prediction. Achieved level 2; required level 4 — largest gap in the assessment."
    },
