      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and operating input parameters must have documented uncertainty bounds; Monte Carlo or equivalent UQ must propagate input uncertainty to NIH predictions with reported confidence intervals.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 500 samples varying viscosity, hematocrit, and rotational speed within ±10% bounds. 95th-percentile NIH predictions remain below clinical threshold at all operating points. However, power-law model coefficients (C, alpha, beta) were treated as fixed constants without uncertainty, representing a significant omission. Achieved level 2; required level 4."
    },
