    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team determined that the five-point validation campaign demonstrates acceptable hemolysis prediction accuracy (all relative errors below 15%) and that Monte Carlo UQ confirms 95th-percentile NIH predictions remain below the clinical threshold. The decision to accept is conditional on the acknowledged gaps being addressed in a subsequent submission. The broken provenance on two validation results (operating points 2 and 4) was noted during review but was not treated as a blocking issue; the experimental data are traceable to the broader FDA pump test campaign documentation.",
